Convinced that we can’t handle disaster , we seek a guide in hopes of avoiding pain because we lack the life skills necessary to navigate uncertainty on our own.
Of course, this is simply a rejection of randomness and uncertainty, an embrace of patternicity that provides a false sense of safety.
It interferes with attaining emotional freedom.” If the uncertainty that comes with living creates such anxiety, why not let patternicity quell those fears?
It is neither existence nor nonexistence, yet exhibits the qualities of both.”Fundamentally, life itself is uncertainty.
Journalist Mark Vernon argues,“The genius of Plato’s Socrates was to embrace ordinary human uncertainty and doubt, and fashion it into a flourishing way of life.